<h2>Applications</h2><h3>Console-based Applications and Tools</h3>
<li><a href="https://cmus.github.io/">cmus</a> - Small, fast and powerful console music player.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/nvbn/thefuck">fuck</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/nvbn/thefuck" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">61.8k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":61810,"repo":"nvbn/thefuck"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Command line tool which corrects your previously mistyped command.</li>
<li><a href="https://nicolargo.github.io/glances/">glances</a> - Cross-platform system monitoring tool.</li>
<li><a href="http://hisham.hm/htop/">htop</a> - Nice looking, customizable task manager.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nano-editor.org">nano</a> - Simple to use text editor.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cgsecurity.org/wiki/PhotoRec">photorec</a> - Useful tool for restoring deleted files.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/ranger/ranger">ranger</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/ranger/ranger" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">9.7k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":9660,"repo":"ranger/ranger"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Vim-inspired file manager for the console.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/KittyKatt/screenFetch">screenFetch</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/KittyKatt/screenFetch" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">3.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":3201,"repo":"KittyKatt/screenFetch"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Fetches system/theme information in terminal.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cgsecurity.org/wiki/TestDisk">testdisk</a> - A tool for disk partition recovery.</li>
<li><a href="http://vim.org">vim</a> - Advanced text editor that seeks to provide the power of the de-facto Unix editor 'Vi', with a more complete feature set.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/uoaerg/wavemon">wavemon</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/uoaerg/wavemon" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">543</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":543,"repo":"uoaerg/wavemon"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Monitoring application for wireless network devices.</li>
<h2>Applications</h2><h4>GNOME-based</h4>
<li><a href="https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Evince">Evince</a> - The most popular document viewer on the GNOME platform.</li>
<li><a href="https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Polari">Polari</a> - IRC client built to be easy to use.</li>
<li><a href="https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Todo">To Do</a> - Minimalistic personal task manager designed to fit right into your GNOME desktop.</li>
<h2>Applications</h2><h4>Pantheon-based</h4>
<li><a href="https://jangernert.github.io/FeedReader/">FeedReader</a> - RSS desktop client able to integrate with multiple online services.</li>
<li><a href="http://parnold-x.github.io/nasc/">NaSC</a> - Intelligent calculator app.</li>
